<!-- ═══════════════════ 3. DATABASE OVERVIEW ═══════════════════ -->
<section class="stack" aria-label="Database architecture overview">
  <h2>Database architecture — what the knowledge store holds</h2>
  <p>Sixteen SOLID-compliant tables in a single SQLite database replace scattered JSONL files. Four logical groups, each with a distinct role. <a href="/db-schema">Explore the full schema →</a></p>

  <div class="db-overview-grid">
    <div class="db-overview-group" style="--grp-color: #8b4513">
      <div class="db-grp-header"><span class="db-grp-icon">⚙</span><strong>Core Pipeline</strong><span class="db-grp-count">6 tables</span></div>
      <ul class="db-grp-tables">
        <li><code>books</code> — one row per ingested source</li>
        <li><code>chapters</code> — each chapter with enrichment state</li>
        <li><code>episodes</code> — output episode registry</li>
        <li><code>phonetics</code> — Islamic name pronunciations</li>
        <li><code>pipeline_runs</code> — audit log of every phase run</li>
        <li><code>cost_ledger</code> — per-call LLM cost tracking</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-overview-group" style="--grp-color: #b8860b">
      <div class="db-grp-header"><span class="db-grp-icon">📚</span><strong>Knowledge Store</strong><span class="db-grp-count">6 tables</span></div>
      <ul class="db-grp-tables">
        <li><code>knowledge_atoms</code> — Quran / Hadith / Doctrine atoms</li>
        <li><code>atom_sources</code> — provenance join table</li>
        <li><code>atom_topic_tags</code> — covering-indexed tag join</li>
        <li><code>external_corpora</code> — Kashkole corpus registry</li>
        <li><code>topic_type_taxonomy</code> — 18 seed rows</li>
        <li><code>corpus_chapters</code> — per-chapter state machine</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-overview-group" style="--grp-color: #4a7c4a">
      <div class="db-grp-header"><span class="db-grp-icon">⚖</span><strong>Quality Audit</strong><span class="db-grp-count">1 table</span></div>
      <ul class="db-grp-tables">
        <li><code>challenger_findings</code> — P0/P1/P2 findings per chapter, fix status, and iteration count</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="db-grp-note">Challenger findings feed the convergence loop and the cross-book health scores in the Bookshelf.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="db-overview-group" style="--grp-color: #5b8dd9">
      <div class="db-grp-header"><span class="db-grp-icon">⚡</span><strong>Source Library Mirror</strong><span class="db-grp-count">4 tables</span><span class="db-grp-wave">Wave J</span></div>
      <ul class="db-grp-tables">
        <li><code>fts_quran</code> — FTS5: Arabic + Pickthall + Asad + Urdu full-text</li>
        <li><code>fts_topics</code> — FTS5: Kashkole topic data full-text search</li>
        <li><code>fts_sessions</code> — FTS5: 343 lecture transcripts</li>
        <li><code>term_index</code> — unified term lookup with etymology, tradition, source</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="db-grp-note">mirror.db — separate from knowledge.db. Gitignored, &lt;50 MB. Auto-populated from SQL Server on first sync. Zero token cost per lookup.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="db-overview-group db-grp-future" style="--grp-color: #5b8dd9">
      <div class="db-grp-header"><span class="db-grp-icon">🌿</span><strong>Etymology</strong><span class="db-grp-count">3 tables</span><span class="db-grp-wave">Wave 3</span></div>
      <ul class="db-grp-tables">
        <li><code>arabic_roots</code> — Semitic roots with abjad sums</li>
        <li><code>word_etymologies</code> — morphological derivations</li>
        <li><code>letter_profiles</code> — 28 rows, makhraj + sifāt</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="db-grp-note">Created now, empty until Wave 3. No migration required.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

